cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.CR 

This paper focuses on the development of a clickbait detector using text-based features. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) as it involves natural language processing techniques. Information Retrieval (cs.IR) is also a possible sub-category as the paper deals with the classification of posts based on their content. Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) is another possible sub-category as the paper deals with social media as a source of news. Cybersecurity (cs.CY) and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) are also possible sub-categories as clickbait posts can be used for malicious purposes such as spreading fake news or phishing attacks.
